  "description": "This dataset examines the effects of theta transcranial alternating current stimulation (tACS) on working memory performance and neural activity. Participants underwent either verum or sham stimulation at 6 Hz applied to frontal-central electrode sites, followed by working memory tasks requiring mental manipulation or retention of items while EEG was recorded. Resting-state EEG data with eyes closed and open were also acquired to characterize baseline neural oscillations.",
  "methods_description": "Transcranial alternating current stimulation (tACS) was applied at 6 Hz, 1 mA intensity to electrode sites Fpz-CPz for 20 minutes (verum or sham). Working memory tasks were performed during concurrent EEG recording. Resting-state EEG was recorded for 3 minutes with eyes closed and 1.5 minutes with eyes open.",
